`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `useRef(moveDirection); moveRef.current = moveDirection` pattern is essential for R3F hooks: `useFrame` captures a closure at mount time, so reading `moveRef.current` (not the prop directly) always gets the latest frame's input without stale values.
- `body.linvel().y` must be preserved when calling `setLinvel` — Rapier doesn't accumulate gravity if you overwrite Y every frame with 0. Only the XZ components are driven by player input.
- When a new hook import is added to a component under test, ALL module-level side effects in that hook (e.g., `new THREE.Vector3()`) run at `import` time in Jest — so the hook itself must be mocked in the component test, even if it's your own code.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

